1
00:00:00,301 --> 00:00:01,251
Previously on "Manhattan"...

2
00:00:01,302 --> 00:00:03,253
Because on July 4th, 1945,

3
00:00:03,988 --> 00:00:06,907
we're going to test the
gadget in our own backyard.

4
00:00:06,908 --> 00:00:09,910
The Army manipulated
us, you and I, Charlie.

5
00:00:10,361 --> 00:00:11,694
We have to stop this train.

6
00:00:11,729 --> 00:00:13,196
He doesn't just want a seat at the table.

7
00:00:13,230 --> 00:00:15,815
He wants to shut down the project.

8
00:00:15,866 --> 00:00:18,568
If you thought you were racing
the Nazis to a super weapon,

9
00:00:18,619 --> 00:00:20,820
your ignorance has been engineered.

10
00:00:20,871 --> 00:00:22,906
I gave up my one shot at history

11
00:00:22,957 --> 00:00:24,457
so you could get us a seat at the table.

12
00:00:24,491 --> 00:00:28,077
You excited to incinerate 20,000 kids?

13
00:00:28,128 --> 00:00:31,130
I think Frank Winter sabotaged the pretest.

14
00:00:31,165 --> 00:00:33,833
This test is the start of a whole new era,

15
00:00:33,884 --> 00:00:37,720
like Auro's interplanetary cruise
ship crash-landing on Jupiter.

16
00:00:37,755 --> 00:00:40,556
- Are you a spy, Jim?
- Uh, Jeannie, wait!

17
00:00:40,591 --> 00:00:42,225
Jim! I'll handle this.

18
00:00:43,894 --> 00:00:45,728
I'm not going to Trinity.

19
00:00:45,763 --> 00:00:47,146
I'm grateful for the opportunities

20
00:00:47,181 --> 00:00:48,731
you've given me here, Charlie,

21
00:00:48,766 --> 00:00:51,901
but I've had enough death for one lifetime.

22
00:00:51,936 --> 00:00:54,687
- Where's Joey?
- He's on his way to Brooklyn.

23
00:00:54,738 --> 00:00:58,441
Juanita's driving him. He's
going to live with my parents.

24
00:00:58,492 --> 00:01:00,193
Keeping him safe from you,

25
00:01:00,244 --> 00:01:01,861
just like you should have been
kept safe from your father!

26
00:01:01,912 --> 00:01:03,863
You think I won't get in
the car and bring him back?

27
00:01:03,914 --> 00:01:06,582
Your test is in 24 hours.

28
00:01:06,617 --> 00:01:08,584
You think I don't know
which way you'll drive?

29
00:01:08,619 --> 00:01:12,372
You, a guy who went to
a second-rate law school,

30
00:01:12,423 --> 00:01:16,042
is getting orchestra
seats to physics history?

31
00:01:16,093 --> 00:01:17,760
You and Perseus

32
00:01:17,795 --> 00:01:19,379
are going to go out
there on your own.

33
00:01:19,430 --> 00:01:21,180
You built the circuits.

34
00:01:21,215 --> 00:01:23,716
You can wire them to go
off at any time you like.

35
00:01:23,767 --> 00:01:27,136
You want to kill the scientists.

36
00:01:27,187 --> 00:01:29,973
You want to kill my friends.

37
00:01:30,024 --> 00:01:32,442
Paul?

38
00:01:32,476 --> 00:01:34,227
We need to talk about Jim.

39
00:01:41,285 --> 00:01:42,785
Last car leaves the blast zone

40
00:01:42,820 --> 00:01:45,405
at zero minus 30 minutes.

41
00:01:45,456 --> 00:01:47,156
They test the firing switch...

42
00:01:47,207 --> 00:01:50,543
Two hours earlier. I know.

43
00:01:50,577 --> 00:01:52,412
So you rig the detonator

44
00:01:52,463 --> 00:01:54,213
to go off when Isaacs hits the switch.

45
00:01:54,248 --> 00:01:57,417
The bomb fizzles and scatters plutonium

46
00:01:57,468 --> 00:01:59,802
halfway to El Paso.

47
00:01:59,837 --> 00:02:01,971
Killing all the staff on the ground.

48
00:02:04,475 --> 00:02:07,810
I think we should stick
to the original plan.

49
00:02:07,845 --> 00:02:10,229
Hold off till everyone evacuates.

50
00:02:10,264 --> 00:02:12,815
Just... just you and me now, right?

51
00:02:12,850 --> 00:02:15,818
The decision is ours.

52
00:02:15,853 --> 00:02:19,022
We're not the directors of this play.

53
00:02:19,073 --> 00:02:22,575
- We're the actors.
- What's your part?

54
00:02:22,609 --> 00:02:24,444
Make sure I do mine?

55
00:02:29,416 --> 00:02:30,917
But where's the proof, Paul,

56
00:02:30,951 --> 00:02:33,252
besides some baseball hat?

57
00:02:33,287 --> 00:02:35,588
Meeks was the most
devoted member of my group.

58
00:02:35,622 --> 00:02:37,256
I practically had to
crowbar him out the door

59
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:39,509
to attend his own mother's funeral.

60
00:02:41,595 --> 00:02:43,296
What?

61
00:03:02,066 --> 00:03:04,283
- Operator. -
Yeah, outside line, please.

62
00:03:04,318 --> 00:03:07,620
Fairview, 89091.

63
00:03:07,654 --> 00:03:10,907
 Hold, please.

64
00:03:12,743 --> 00:03:14,327
Hello?

65
00:03:15,662 --> 00:03:17,797
Yes, hello.

66
00:03:17,831 --> 00:03:19,332
Who am I speaking with?

67
00:03:19,383 --> 00:03:21,918
This is Edith Meeks.

68
00:03:24,755 --> 00:03:27,140
I'm very sorry to
trouble you, ma'am.

69
00:03:29,343 --> 00:03:31,310
Is Jim Meeks your son?

70
00:03:31,345 --> 00:03:32,845
Yes, he is.

71
00:03:32,896 --> 00:03:35,314
Are you a friend of Jimmy's?

72
00:03:35,349 --> 00:03:38,985
No, I... I was his teacher.

73
00:03:40,938 --> 00:03:43,022
He's going to wind up
in the electric chair.

74
00:03:43,073 --> 00:03:44,824
God, Frank, Colonel Darrow finds out,

75
00:03:44,858 --> 00:03:47,527
he won't make it that far, believe me.

76
00:03:47,578 --> 00:03:49,495
- Who else knows?
- No one.

77
00:03:49,530 --> 00:03:51,664
And as soon as it's out of
the bag, he's beyond our help.

78
00:03:51,698 --> 00:03:54,033
A spy in the hand is worth 10 in the grave.

79
00:03:54,084 --> 00:03:56,335
We can flip him double agency.

80
00:03:56,370 --> 00:03:58,121
The Soviets have been doing it for decades.

81
00:03:58,172 --> 00:03:59,922
We've just joined the game.

82
00:03:59,957 --> 00:04:01,541
We?

83
00:04:01,592 --> 00:04:04,377
I may have picked up some extracurriculars.

84
00:04:08,715 --> 00:04:10,049
Listen to me, all right?

85
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:12,135
Intelligence boys will
play poker with a spy,

86
00:04:12,186 --> 00:04:13,352
but not with a saboteur,

87
00:04:13,387 --> 00:04:15,221
so we have one chance to save him.

88
00:04:15,272 --> 00:04:18,107
We'll get to Jim before
he gets to the bomb.

89
00:04:18,142 --> 00:04:19,809
We're looking for Dr. Frank Winter.

90
00:04:19,860 --> 00:04:21,811
Is this his desk?

91
00:04:21,862 --> 00:04:23,396
Where's Frank Winter?

92
00:04:23,447 --> 00:04:25,364
Damn it. Helen.

93
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:29,202
I may have dabbled in some
extracurriculars myself.

94
00:04:29,236 --> 00:04:30,987
Why did you think I came to you first?

95
00:04:36,627 --> 00:04:39,295
They're my friends, the scientists.

96
00:04:39,329 --> 00:04:41,080
Well, they're also mass murderers.

97
00:04:41,131 --> 00:04:42,965
You can do better.

98
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,718
