call the game for rain.

148
00:07:38,091 --> 00:07:39,975
Let's just hope it blows over.

149
00:07:40,010 --> 00:07:43,312
It'll blow radioactive fallout
from Roswell to Socorro.

150
00:07:43,347 --> 00:07:44,814
I'm sympathetic. The Army isn't.

151
00:07:44,848 --> 00:07:46,849
Either way, I take responsibility.

152
00:07:50,854 --> 00:07:53,522
Hey. Where you been?

153
00:07:53,573 --> 00:07:54,857
You all right, pal?

154
00:07:54,908 --> 00:07:56,609
Yeah, I got a...

155
00:07:56,611 --> 00:07:58,911
I got a flat tire on the way up.

156
00:07:58,945 --> 00:08:00,162
Oh.

157
00:08:00,197 --> 00:08:01,497
I'm supposed to check the...

158
00:08:01,531 --> 00:08:03,165
The detonator circuits.

159
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:05,284
I think they already took care of it.

160
00:08:07,087 --> 00:08:09,038
So it's, it's happening?

161
00:08:09,089 --> 00:08:11,507
Right now?

162
00:08:11,541 --> 00:08:14,543
In the face of reason
and safety precautions.

163
00:08:14,594 --> 00:08:16,796
Welcome to Jupiter.

164
00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:32,478
From Oppenheimer.

165
00:08:39,118 --> 00:08:41,118
_

166
00:08:47,661 --> 00:08:51,464
You want a volunteer to climb
a 100-foot steel lightning rod?

167
